Sentencas: Sr2-xBaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (x = 0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1) perovskite materials have been prepared as potential cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) via a sol-gel combustion method.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) confirms that the expansion of the unit cell derived from the substitution of the large radius Ba atom, with the impurity phase structure only being detected when x = 0.8 and 1.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Concurrently, thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) increase with increasing Ba doping.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectrometry (XPS) measurements show that A-site doped Ba in the perovskite has an insignificant impact on the existence and ratio of Fe2+/Fe3+ and Mo6+/Mo5+ species within the Sr2-xBaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (x = 0.2, 0.4, 0.6) (SBFM) samples.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta, the SBFM cathodes exhibited better electrochemical performance, which has been confirmed by the electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS).
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, Sr1.8Ba0.2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SB0.2FM) shows the lowest interface polarization (R-p).
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore the peak power densities of single cells based on the SB0.2FM cathode are 0.87 and 1.30 W cm(-2) at 700 and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All these results suggest that SBFM materials are promising cathodes for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A new family of barium-doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ perovskites for application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
